insanely hard, no matter which way you slice it, and<br>
what with the new dwarfish elf guards for Jaggedpine, <br>
I don't know if I'd be KOS to them or not. *growls*<br>
<br>
So I'm debating the merits of three classes that can be<br>
Half-Elves.  Half Elves are my favorite race in the game, and they're very handy on FV because they speak both<br>
Elvish and Human Tongue fluently at level 1! :-)<br>
<br>
Paladin:  Gets experience resurrections at level 30.  Uhh...gets Cleric buffs.  Uhhh...gets Lay On Hands<br>
and healing spells.  Uhh...is this class easy to play?<br>
<br>
Ranger:  Gets Forage, superior Track skill, Snare, Camouflage, and various cool Druid spells like SoW.<br>
Are Rangers easy to play, or are they kind of hard?<br>
<br>
Bard:  I like Bards a lot, plus they can worship Solusek<br>
Ro and Veeshan and STILL wear plate armor.  They get songs for everything except port (like Druids) and Rez.<br>
Of all the classes except Bertoxx Cleric, I've had a lot of fun with their roleplay potential.  The big downside:<br>
<br>
Twisting is hard, plus no matter how hard I try, twisting<br>
4, 5, or 6+ songs eludes me.  *sigh*<br>
<br>
Which Half-Elf class is the easiest to play of these 3?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Rhaxalygen<br>
Cheers to Ulec for being the ONLY Bertoxxulous Cleric<br>
I know who's made it to 60!  Take THAT, Innoruuk!!! ;-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 9:44:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Easiest class to play:  Paladin, Ranger, or Bard?</span><hr size=1> Bard is right out. There's lots of nuances to being a bard.<br>
