<br>
Bard - Nice class, forage, track, dual wield, armor and the songs.  Get stronger as they go along and desired by groups.  Problem is the songs, you are always glued to the screen to be an effective bard.  Bards always made either my neck or hand hurt.  If you can handle em they are great, if you dont like to twist and always switch items/targets then something else is for you.<br>
<br>
Paladins - Probably the easiest to play in terms of simplicity.  Great armor selection, heals, stuns, etc.  Good to roleplay, imo.  Paladins are straight forward: don the armor, equip the 2HS (or whatever), go kill the baddies, help old ladies cross the street when done.  Nuff said.<br>
<br>
Rangers - Can be addictive with forage, track (the REAL kind), good buffs, heals, SoW (eventually) and the fun of using a bow for more than the one shot pull.  Problem is a ranger's role changes as the levels go up.  If you can learn your strengths and shortcomings at each stage, rangers are great - they become completely different starting at lvl 40, which is where you stop soloing anything that cant be affected by panic animal, and change into a death machine with enough AA points under your belt.<br>
<br>
So to sum up -<br>
<br>
Bards - Best of the three if you can handle the micro management<br>
Paladins - Probably the easiest to play (IMO)<br>
Rangers - You're going to die a lot learning how to do it right, but worth the trip <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uboshile.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boshile</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 2:25:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Easiest class to play:  Paladin, Ranger, or Bard?</span><hr size=1> I have never played a Pally except for a few levels and I didnt like the way I had to play so I rolled a ranger I am now 53 and let me tell you it is a very good glass to play. <br>
<br>
If you think just a second of what we can do... But problem is on raids we have less AC and less HP so we tend to be left out since they say we are weak. hrmm well we deal pretty decent damage, we control aggro and take aggro, How many times have I saved a casters or clerics or even chanter life cause the warrior couldnt taunt? countless .<br>
<br>
But then how many times did I die cause tank cant take back aggro from me. Even using jolt and not hitting dumb mob Ouch I still get a beating!<br>
<br>
Another thing I like doing is when mob runs to whack on our casters clicky spell and wham he turns back on me just fun to see him run from one player to another to decide on who he hates most. But in the end they hate me most <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
So play ranger if you want action but dont complain if you get no groups. At 53 some groups will put a level 48 tank in main group saying that he is better than a 53 ranger .... go figure.... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uboshile.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boshile</A> at: 8/8/02 2:26:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukironkeensong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiron Keensong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 2:57:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> twisting fairy tale</span><hr size=1> one word on Bards:<br>
<br>
you mentioned twisting 4 or more songs. forget it. its a fairy tale brought up by some braggarts. you cannot twist 4+ songs efficiently. even with a *perfect* connection and a strong machine you simply cannot hold those songs. not in a group, not on raids. maybe when soloing (but you better keep Selo's out of the twist). most bards refere on twisting 4+ songs when using a processing item like BoH or any other item with a bard song effect. also, there are only a few situation where you would need to twist more then 3 songs.<br>
<br>
if you can keep 3 songs up and running you're fine.<br>
<br>
Bards are a fine class, we can do almost everything. but we are masters of nothing. <p><b>~Kiron MacNight</b><br><i>Twilight Bastion<br>Firiona Vie<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243721>Bardic Crap</a></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 3:21:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The best bards can regularly do 4 songs</span><hr size=1> I usually expect any 60 bard to be able to do 3 and good ones can twist 4 while keeping things mez'd.  I rarely see 5 twisted.  The trick is to use a gamepad and automate the twist.  I suppose you might be able to do it with macros, too, but most of the good bards I know use a gamepad for it -- you can just press one button and your twist will just keep running forever until you turn it off.<br>
<br>
Like many of the various tools that improve on the EQ UI, gamepads and programable keyboards are considered cheating by VI and if you admit to using one to a GM, they'll ban you (yup, even if you're handicapped and you NEED that device to even play).  However, use of programmable input devices is not detectable by EQ.  So, like other well known UI tools, don't admit to using it.<br>
<br>
This is not to say twisting is easy, just that 4 is not as uncommon as you think.  You still have to program that gamepad and be ready to remem and reconfigure your songs to work with all the automation you've setup to help you.  This is pretty far from easy and all that overhead is why I cringe at even the thought of playing a bard.<br>
<br>
Good bards are incredible for groups and raids, but they're definitely not an easy class to play well.  I'd have to vote with the others and say a ranger is the easiest of pal, rng, and brd. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"I will gladly pay you Tuesday for Sushi today!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1087<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 4:39:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The best bards can regularly do 4 songs</span><hr size=1> Don't bards get an AA to make songs last longer, thus allowing massive twisting?<br>
