<br>
eqdiva is FULL of threads where experienced bards debate whether it is even possible to twist more than 3 songs, or whether four songs is just a pipe dream due to delayed graphics.<br>
<br>
if the experts cannot agree, then neither do i expect us to arrive at a solution here.<br>
<br>
i'm a very VERY inexperienced player.  my highest level ever was 30 on my ranger.  i've never played paladin, they don't seem interesting to me at all, and i'm no goodie-goodie.  i play a bardling now, and although i'm VERY bad at it, i can tell you that it is a bazillion times more difficult than a ranger.<br>
<br>
ever play a rogue?  i've read that a good rogue is hitting so many buttons and switching items in and out for that killer backstab, etc.  that their fingers tend to hurt at the end of the night.  well, i've never really played a rogue, but i'm assuming that bards are just as, if not more, intense. <br>
<br>
you'll be hitting 3 keys every 18 seconds.  in addition, you may be switching between instruments every 3 seconds, or between instruments and two weapons every 3 seconds.  the instruments have to go with the song, of course.  and many times you'll be debating with yourself whether it's better to give the boost that an instrument gives to your health regen and magic resist songs, or smack that goblin wizard with your sword to make it stop hurting your party members all the quicker.  much to do and many decisions to make as a bard.  <br>
<br>
you'll have to pay attention to WHICH songs you're playing.  you can't just set up the three that you think best and twist them through the night.  melee mobs are going to take different songs than caster mobs.  i have two separate twists for these, and you've got to remember to switch them on the fly, second by second through the night depending upon your 'audience'. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
you've also got to take into account who is in your group.  melee characters aren't going to get much use out of that mana song, and i doubt that haste helps wizards much (?).  your song lineup can and will change drastically from place to place and even group to group.  this is as it should be, you're a performer after all. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
this is VERY different from a ranger.  rangers bag their assortment of weapons and arrows, load up their spells and are pretty much done preparing for the evening.  run for the nearest port terminal, snare, hit Attack, heal.  as they say, rinse-repeat-finis.<br>
<br>
you want ease of play, go ranger.  i could probably fall asleep on the keyboard with my ranger, and no one would be any the wiser.  you want fly-by-the-seat-of-your-pants, ohgodswhat the HELL am i supposed to be doing right now excitement, pick bard.<br>
<br>
just remember, chatting and bards don't mix.  i'm relearning this every day.  if you want to have an extensive  &amp; chatty social life, you'd better either be able to type 120wpm or give up hunting altogether as a bard.  chatting kills me.  ohwell, already admitted i'm not a very skilled bard.<br>
<br>
